-- Brazil Expects $235 Billion in Renewable Energy During Decade
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-09-24T21:05:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/brazil-expects-235-billion-in-renewable-energy-during-decade.html
Brazil will see $235 billion of
investments in  renewable-energy  and biofuel projects during the
next ten years, Edison Lobao, the country’s mines and energy
minister, said today at a United Nations event on sustainable
energy in New York.  The nation will install 36 gigawatts of hydroeletric
plants, 12 gigawatts of biomass plants and 11 gigawatts of wind
farms during that time, according to a transcript of the
minister’s speech acquired by  Bloomberg News .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
